RESUMO-CV.TEXTO-RESUMO-CV-RH: PhD degree from Higher Polytechnic School of University of Salamanca (USAL), Spain, in cooperation with Polytechnic School of University of So Paulo (EP-USP), Brazil, in structures. Master's degree in structural engineering from University Roma Tre (UNIROMA3), Italy. Bachelor's degree in civil engineering from UNIROMA3. 10 grants/scholarships, with two of them for stays in public Brazilian R&D centers: EP-USP (2 years) and So Paulo State University (UNESP) (4 years). Reviewer of WoS and SCOPUS journals, researcher in the group of "Dynamic experimental analysis of structures" at EP-USP and member of the "Portuguese society of seismic engineering (SPES)". Six-year work experience in engineering, especially in the major area of civil projects and structures, hydraulic engineering and road infrastructure. Civil engineer and job leader in national and international companies. 13 technical projects and 3 academic projects. PhD student at UNESP in Structures. Researcher with several scientific papers published in high impact journals and presentations at congresses.
RESUMO-CV.TEXTO-RESUMO-CV-RH-EN: I received a Master?s Degree in Structural Engineering from Universit degli Studi Roma Tre (Rome, Italy), where I also held a scholarship as an instructor in Computing. I am graduated in Civil Engineering at the same university. For one year, I was an exchange student with a scholarship at Escola Politcnica da Universidade de So Paulo, having attended four disciplines. I have a four-year work experience in the area of Engineering, especially in the major area of civil projects, structures, and in the areas of hydraulic engineering and road infrastructure. I worked as a Civil Engineer in the following companies: "CFPS Engenharia e Projetos S.A." and "EGT Engenharia Ltda", in So Paulo, Brazil; and at "STADE S.r.l.", in Rome, Italy.

PROJETO-DE-PESQUISA.NOME-DO-PROJETO: Experimental and numerical study about the geometric nonlinearity on vibrations of rotating machines support structures
PROJETO-DE-PESQUISA.DESCRICAO-DO-PROJETO: Neste projeto conjunto CECS/UFABC e EPUSP, pretende-se estudar o efeito da no linearidade geomtrica sobre as vibraes de estruturas de suporte de mquinas rotativas. Objetivos: 1) revisar a literatura sobre os efeitos da no linearidade geomtrica considerando o comportamento dinmico de estruturas excitadas por carregamentos peridicos; 2) propor modelos matemticos de poucos graus de liberdade via formulao Lagrangeana, e anlise dos sistemas de equaes diferenciais no lineares resultantes por mtodos de perturbao e por integrao numrica passo-a-passo no tempo; 3) produzir histricos de resposta, planos de fase, estudo da estabilidade, mapas de Poincar, diagramas de bifurcao, bacias de atrao, expoentes de Lyapunov; 4) montar aparato de ensaio dinmico de modelos fsicos de estruturas de suporte de equipamentos rotativos; 5) realizar ensaios dinmicos de modelos fsicos em escala de estruturas de suporte de mquinas rotativas; 6) montar e analisar modelos numricos via mtodo dos elementos finitos, balizados pelos modelos matemticos e fsicos, utilizando programas comerciais e acadmicos. Total do projeto: R$ 79.150,00
